  <title>Date Literals</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Date</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Date Literals</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">Date literals are formatted </para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><tab /><text styleclass="Code Example" style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;">YYYY.MM.DD</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">Examples:</para>
    <para styleclass="Code Example"><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;"> &#160; 2000.01.01</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;"> &#160; 2012.02.29</text><br/><text style="font-weight:normal; font-style:normal; color:#000000;"> &#160; 2015.09.25</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text">Of course you can also use runtime functions to construct a literal, such as STOD(&quot;20150925&quot;) or ConDate(2019,9,25) but a literal is more efficient.</para>
  </body>
